Hi,<br />
<br />
What needs to be done so I can target the right hand side of the ModernTab List using the Click method of a Button or [url=...] code of a BBCodeBlock?<br />
<br />
I have a ModernTab List that I would like to add a button to in the StatusMargin grid, and I would like the button's target to be the same ModernFrame as the LinkList.<br />
<br />
Everything I've tried so far has instead targetted either the frame containing the ModernTab or the ModernWindow.<br />
<pre><code>&lt;Grid Style=&quot;{StaticResource ContentRoot}&quot;&gt;
        &lt;mui:ModernTab Layout=&quot;List&quot; x:Name=&quot;labelLinks&quot;&gt;&lt;/mui:ModernTab&gt;
        &lt;!-- new label button --&gt;
        &lt;Grid Margin=&quot;{StaticResource StatusMargin}&quot; HorizontalAlignment=&quot;Left&quot; VerticalAlignment=&quot;Bottom&quot;&gt;
            &lt;Rectangle /&gt;
            &lt;mui:BBCodeBlock Margin=&quot;16,0,0,0&quot; BBCode=&quot;[url=/Pages/NewLabel.xaml]new label[/url]&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;/Grid&gt;
    &lt;/Grid&gt;</code></pre>

Thanks for any help you're able to provide.<br />
